The paper deals with compressed sensing (CS) and proposes a robust iterative hard thresholding (IHT) algorithm for reconstructing sparse signals in the presence of impulsive noise. It also incorporates prior signal information in the recovery process, specifically studying the case of CS with partially known support. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also involves signal processing (cs.SP), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical theory (cs.SI) in its approach and analysis.
